item.title: Mechscape renamed to stellar dawn
item.dc:creator: @abraham2119 abraham2119
item.description:
@abraham2119 wrote:

[quote=“Starting up …, post:20, topic:299647”]Why do they stick with with browser based bull shit?[/quote]because its the simplest way

but for people who want to play it without having the need to go to their site and load the game, jagex implemented a main() method in client.class so it would be easy for one to do so. you simply download runescape.jar add a manifest file to it (stating that ‘client’ is the main class), and run it with needed parameters

item.dc:creator: @Unhandled Unhandled
item.description:
@Unhandled wrote:

I recall Jagex stating Mechscape uses technology a generation ahead of Runescape, I’m pretty sure they said this after HD came out, but I could be wrong. I also doubt they meant RuneTek 5 as that isn’t really new technology.
Their statement doesn’t really follow with them using the same client for rs and mechscape, but it would appear that is what they are doing.

item.title: Mechscape renamed to stellar dawn
item.dc:creator: @abraham2119 abraham2119

I wonder if its going to be like Runescape with discontinued items, Like a classic version and later on a 2.0 version, etc…

They won’t make that mistake twice.
[/quote]Maybe people will find exploits?[/quote]actually, i believe its the opposite. they are using the same fucking client as the runescape client (except cache will be different ofc), and i suppose the game server will have the same structure as runescape’s. as far as macro detection and such is concerned, they will obviously be implementing the same methods they use in runescape. if youve read the few interviews gower has had, youll see theyve been working around 4 years (i think) on it, and its about done, but theyve been in testing for a while
